  "A student compares two toy rockets. Rocket A has a mass of 0.5 kg and Rocket B has a mass of 1.5 kg. Both are launched with the same 15 N of thrust. Which statement is correct?": "",
  "Both rockets accelerate at the same rate since the force is identical": "",
  "Rocket A accelerates three times faster because it has one-third the mass": "",
  "Rocket B accelerates faster because heavier objects fall with more force": "",
  "Neither rocket can accelerate because 15 N is not enough total force": "",
  "Rocket A: a = 15 N / 0.5 kg = 30 m/s². Rocket B: a = 15 N / 1.5 kg = 10 m/s². Rocket A accelerates three times faster because it has one-third the mass. With the same force, less mass means more acceleration (F = ma).": ""
